    {
      "parameters": {
        "content": "# Handle chat messages at scale for FAQ Bots\n\n**Pattern:** Chatbot Responder · **Level:** Foundation · **Trigger:** Chat\n\n## What it does\nHandle chat messages at scale for FAQ Bots. It responds live to chat messages.\n\n## Why it exists\nManual faq bots is slow and error-prone; this workflow makes the process repeatable, monitored and hands-off, with failures surfaced instead of silently lost.\n\n## Main flow\nWhen Chat Message Received → Frame the Assignment → Coordinator Agent → Unpack Sections → Persist Deliverable to Google Sheets → Send Summary to Slack\n\n## Use it for\n- Teams that want to chatbot responder without manual effort\n- Anyone automating faq bots in customer support\n- Replacing a fragile manual process with a reliable workflow\n\n## You get\n- Saves hours of manual work each week\n- Standardizes the process every time\n- Keeps your systems in sync\n\n## Before first run\nConnect credentials: Anthropic API key; Google OAuth2 / service account; Slack OAuth2.\nFollow the color key: 🟦 entry · 🟪 AI · 🟫 actions · ⬜ utilities · 🟩 outputs · 🟥 error rail.\nEach node has its own doc card underneath — read those before editing.",
        "width": 480,
        "height": 900
      },
      "type": "n8n-nodes-base.stickyNote",
      "typeVersion": 1,
      "position": [
        -830,
        80
      ],
      "id": "fa4367eb-def5-1d61-06db-1d6087568470",
      "name": "📘 Workflow Overview"
    },
    {
      "parameters": {
        "content": "## 🤖 AI cluster\n\nPurple nodes form one AI unit: the root node orchestrates, sub-nodes plug in via typed ports (model / memory / tools / parser). Swap the chat model without rewiring anything else. Costs scale with tokens — keep prompts lean and cap iterations.",
        "width": 360,
        "height": 260,
        "color": 6
      },
      "type": "n8n-nodes-base.stickyNote",
      "typeVersion": 1,
      "position": [
        -230,
        -20
      ],
      "id": "eae31fbc-5ea5-d32e-37b0-0b87e41bf2bd",
      "name": "🤖 AI cluster"
    },
    {
      "parameters": {
        "content": "## 🛠 Customize me\n\nQuick wins: point the data nodes at your own accounts (see 🔑 lines on each card), adjust the trigger cadence, and tune thresholds/labels to your faq bots process. Every node card explains its role — safe to extend at any marked branch.",
        "width": 360,
        "height": 260,
        "color": 4
      },
      "type": "n8n-nodes-base.stickyNote",
